<br>
I wasn't terribly thrilled with the outpouring of negative responses to the piece.. as if we aren't inundated with positive Christian and Jewish pieces *all* *the* *time*.  I chalk it up to fear and pre-opinions, people don't want to find out anything good about Islam, they don't want a &quot;human face&quot; on Muslims; I think people in general enjoy having an &quot;other&quot; they can look to to blame for the woes of life.  In the Middle East it's the West, and in the West it's the Muslims, and no one seems to want to step back and learn about each other in an objective way.<br>
